# --- Local dev (Vite dev server) ---
# Target of the Vite dev-server proxy for /api requests (the Donely backend).
VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:3001

# --- Vercel / static build ---
# Absolute backend URL baked into the build. Leave unset for local dev (falls back to
# '/api' + the dev proxy above). Required for a static Vercel deploy since there is no
# dev-server proxy in production. Include the /api path segment.
# VITE_API_URL=https://donely-backend.vercel.app/api

# --- Brand (100% frontend-owned — see src/brand.ts) ---
# Swapping the brand for a white-label re-skin = set these and redeploy the frontend. No backend
# involvement, no code edit. `GET /api/config` only ever supplies economic values (currency, tax
# rate, payment methods, supported locales); brand name/links never come from the backend.
# Display name + wordmark text. Default 'Donely'.
# VITE_APP_NAME=Donely
# App Store link (wordmark / store badges). Default '#'.
# VITE_APP_STORE_URL=https://apps.apple.com/app/idXXXXXXXXX
# Google Play link (wordmark / store badges). Default '#'.
# VITE_GOOGLE_PLAY_URL=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.example.app

# --- Theme accent (100% frontend-owned — see src/theme.ts) ---
# Named palette: one of violet (default) | teal | blue | rose | emerald | amber | orange.
# `orange` is the "orange dark" marketing theme (matches simplybj.com): warm near-black page
# background + a coral→orange gradient on primary CTA buttons in dark mode.
# VITE_THEME=violet
# Optional hex override for just the resolved palette's accent color (leaves hover/ink/tint/glow
# from the chosen VITE_THEME palette untouched).
# VITE_ACCENT=#7a4fc0
# Forces the marketing site (landing `/`, subpages, `/login`) into dark mode and hides the
# sun/moon dark-mode toggle in the header — for shipping a single-look marketing site (e.g. the
# `orange` theme above is designed dark-only). Fully reversible: unset (the default) and the site
# behaves exactly as before — light by default, with a working light/dark toggle.
# VITE_FORCE_DARK=true
